00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:02.920 align:middle line:90%
Is it less difficult for you?

00:36:02.920 --> 00:36:04.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, profoundly.

00:36:04.770 --> 00:36:10.150 align:middle line:10%
And I think it's a combination
of older and wiser, years

00:36:10.150 --> 00:36:15.280 align:middle line:10%
of working on myself through
meditation and psychotherapy,

00:36:15.280 --> 00:36:19.690 align:middle line:10%
the fact that my three children
are grown up and in college

00:36:19.690 --> 00:36:21.250 align:middle line:10%
and doing well.

00:36:21.250 --> 00:36:28.420 align:middle line:84%
And raising kids is
a daily difficulty

00:36:28.420 --> 00:36:31.060 align:middle line:90%
and takes a lot of energy.

00:36:31.060 --> 00:36:34.240 align:middle line:90%
And my-- I have--

00:36:34.240 --> 00:36:38.560 align:middle line:84%
my second marriage is built
on the foundation of both

00:36:38.560 --> 00:36:41.140 align:middle line:84%
of our spiritual
work, which is a joy

00:36:41.140 --> 00:36:47.050 align:middle line:84%
to share the journey
with one's mate,

00:36:47.050 --> 00:36:52.060 align:middle line:84%
and bearing the fruits of
having gone through the journey.

00:36:52.060 --> 00:36:54.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Was the book difficult
for you to write?

00:36:54.730 --> 00:36:56.770 align:middle line:90%
Was it a hard task?

00:36:56.770 --> 00:37:00.100 align:middle line:84%
>> When I was writing the book,
my father died in the middle

00:37:00.100 --> 00:37:01.700 align:middle line:90%
of writing the book.

00:37:01.700 --> 00:37:05.770 align:middle line:84%
So I was in the
rhythm of writing.

00:37:05.770 --> 00:37:08.650 align:middle line:84%
And I was able to
use writing to get me

00:37:08.650 --> 00:37:11.580 align:middle line:84%
through the grief
of losing my father.

00:37:11.580 --> 00:37:14.800 align:middle line:84%
And I think that was
a great boon to me

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:16.840 align:middle line:90%
to be able to write it down.

00:37:16.840 --> 00:37:21.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Particularly since I know
your father was as difficult

00:37:21.040 --> 00:37:24.150 align:middle line:90%
a man as he was a lovable man.

00:37:24.150 --> 00:37:26.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:37:26.530 --> 00:37:27.400 align:middle line:90%
Yes, he was.

00:37:27.400 --> 00:37:33.430 align:middle line:84%
And I was able to use
writing about my feelings.

00:37:33.430 --> 00:37:38.650 align:middle line:84%
When a parent dies or when
someone you love dies,

00:37:38.650 --> 00:37:41.620 align:middle line:84%
your whole life with
them is churned up.

00:37:41.620 --> 00:37:42.860 align:middle line:90%
It's cultivated again.

00:37:42.860 --> 00:37:44.360 align:middle line:90%
So you get to relive.

00:37:44.360 --> 00:37:47.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've relived
some aspects of my life

00:37:47.410 --> 00:37:50.980 align:middle line:84%
with my father that
I had forgotten.

00:37:50.980 --> 00:37:54.760 align:middle line:84%
Writing about it and just
letting myself really

00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:58.520 align:middle line:90%
feel it was very healing.

00:37:58.520 --> 00:38:00.910 align:middle line:84%
I felt I was able to
really go through it.

00:38:00.910 --> 00:38:04.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Along the way, one of
the friends you met is a man

00:38:04.630 --> 00:38:09.190 align:middle line:84%
by the name of Baba Olatunji
who was so helpful to you when

00:38:09.190 --> 00:38:10.720 align:middle line:90%
your father died.

00:38:10.720 --> 00:38:17.990 align:middle line:84%
>> When my father died, I asked
Baba, how should I do this?

00:38:17.990 --> 00:38:22.220 align:middle line:84%
How can I create a ceremony
that will speak to everyone?

00:38:22.220 --> 00:38:26.300 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well,
in my village,

00:38:26.300 --> 00:38:28.610 align:middle line:90%
every person had a song.

00:38:28.610 --> 00:38:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And when they passed,
we sing the song.

00:38:31.880 --> 00:38:34.910 align:middle line:84%
And that escorts their
spirit into the other world.

00:38:34.910 --> 00:38:36.860 align:middle line:90%
What was your father's song?

00:38:36.860 --> 00:38:38.660 align:middle line:84%
And sure enough,
when it came time

00:38:38.660 --> 00:38:42.590 align:middle line:84%
in the memorial service for
me to give my little speech,

00:38:42.590 --> 00:38:46.640 align:middle line:84%
I said, and now I'm going
to sing my father's song.

00:38:46.640 --> 00:38:49.310 align:middle line:84%
Does anybody know what
my father's song is?

00:38:49.310 --> 00:38:51.440 align:middle line:84%
And all my sisters,
my three sisters,

00:38:51.440 --> 00:38:53.750 align:middle line:90%
chimed in right on beat.

00:38:53.750 --> 00:38:54.890 align:middle line:90%
They knew nothing about it.

00:38:54.890 --> 00:38:55.932 align:middle line:90%
But they chimed right in.

00:38:55.932 --> 00:38:59.660 align:middle line:84%
[VOCALIZING] So we
sang that for a while

00:38:59.660 --> 00:39:02.810 align:middle line:90%
and escorted his spirit on.

00:39:02.810 --> 00:39:09.050 align:middle line:84%
>> It's interesting how many
people in my peer group today

00:39:09.050 --> 00:39:10.940 align:middle line:84%
are asking questions
about death.

00:39:10.940 --> 00:39:13.170 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden,
they're aware of it.

00:39:13.170 --> 00:39:14.412 align:middle line:90%
They're afraid of it.

00:39:14.412 --> 00:39:15.620 align:middle line:90%
They have questions about it.

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:18.740 align:middle line:90%


00:39:18.740 --> 00:39:24.500 align:middle line:90%
Is that answerable these days?

00:39:24.500 --> 00:39:28.100 align:middle line:84%
>> If we're looking for an
answer like this is where we go

00:39:28.100 --> 00:39:31.550 align:middle line:84%
when we die, it's not
answerable because I think

00:39:31.550 --> 00:39:33.410 align:middle line:90%
it's the ultimate mystery.

00:39:33.410 --> 00:39:37.160 align:middle line:84%
And what the
spiritual path does is

00:39:37.160 --> 00:39:41.540 align:middle line:84%
it gives you the ability to
relax into that mystery instead

00:39:41.540 --> 00:39:44.690 align:middle line:84%
of closing down to it
out of fear or just

00:39:44.690 --> 00:39:48.290 align:middle line:84%
out of not knowing what to
do with such an unknown.

00:39:48.290 --> 00:39:54.110 align:middle line:84%
To be able to relax one's
idea of what it might be like

00:39:54.110 --> 00:39:57.410 align:middle line:84%
and just to stand before
it with a sense of openness

00:39:57.410 --> 00:40:03.870 align:middle line:84%
and reverence and awe makes
life much more wonderful.

00:40:03.870 --> 00:40:09.270 align:middle line:84%
And how to practice that so
that you can be open to death

00:40:09.270 --> 00:40:12.000 align:middle line:84%
is first of all,
it's such a shame

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:15.360 align:middle line:84%
that people die now in
hospitals or in nursing homes.

00:40:15.360 --> 00:40:17.850 align:middle line:84%
And we don't get to be
with people when they die.

00:40:17.850 --> 00:40:21.300 align:middle line:84%
I have been with several
people as they die and take

00:40:21.300 --> 00:40:22.290 align:middle line:90%
their last breath.

00:40:22.290 --> 00:40:25.860 align:middle line:84%
And I can tell you, if
anything has helped me

00:40:25.860 --> 00:40:28.320 align:middle line:84%
with my anxiety
about dying, it's

00:40:28.320 --> 00:40:30.450 align:middle line:90%
being with people as they die.

00:40:30.450 --> 00:40:33.960 align:middle line:84%
>> You were with your
best friend when she died.

00:40:33.960 --> 00:40:35.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Of leukemia.

00:40:35.280 --> 00:40:38.940 align:middle line:84%
And that was my first--
the first person

00:40:38.940 --> 00:40:42.200 align:middle line:90%
I was with as she died.

00:40:42.200 --> 00:40:46.470 align:middle line:84%
And I felt I went a little
way with her into whatever

00:40:46.470 --> 00:40:47.940 align:middle line:90%
the next world is.

00:40:47.940 --> 00:40:54.480 align:middle line:84%
And it gave me a
sense of confidence

00:40:54.480 --> 00:40:57.970 align:middle line:90%
in the eternity of the soul.

00:40:57.970 --> 00:41:01.600 align:middle line:84%
And since then, I've been
with other people as they die.

00:41:01.600 --> 00:41:04.690 align:middle line:90%
And I recommend it highly.

00:41:04.690 --> 00:41:07.600 align:middle line:84%
>> It's greatly comforting
to hear you say that,

00:41:07.600 --> 00:41:11.180 align:middle line:84%
to hear you say, it gave
me a sense of confidence.

00:41:11.180 --> 00:41:15.910 align:middle line:84%
Because when someone is
with someone when they die,

00:41:15.910 --> 00:41:21.010 align:middle line:84%
we are all afraid that the
sense it will give us is sorrow.

00:41:21.010 --> 00:41:22.510 align:middle line:84%
But that's not what
you experienced,

00:41:22.510 --> 00:41:24.190 align:middle line:84%
even though she was your
best friend, someone

00:41:24.190 --> 00:41:25.100 align:middle line:90%
you loved for years.

00:41:25.100 --> 00:41:32.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I sensed her
rejoining the undivided sense

00:41:32.910 --> 00:41:34.740 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:41:34.740 --> 00:41:41.580 align:middle line:84%
I sensed her being freed
from the condensed life

00:41:41.580 --> 00:41:44.070 align:middle line:90%
we live in the body.

00:41:44.070 --> 00:41:48.150 align:middle line:84%
And it's hard to wrap
words around what I sensed.

00:41:48.150 --> 00:41:51.840 align:middle line:84%
And it begins to sound
like something contrived.

00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:55.140 align:middle line:84%
But in moments of
meditation, and when

00:41:55.140 --> 00:41:57.930 align:middle line:84%
I am with people who
are dying, or when

00:41:57.930 --> 00:42:00.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm listening to
great gospel music

00:42:00.150 --> 00:42:05.160 align:middle line:84%
or taking a walk in nature, and
I feel that sense of oneness

00:42:05.160 --> 00:42:11.130 align:middle line:84%
with everything that is, that's
when my resistance to death

00:42:11.130 --> 00:42:12.240 align:middle line:90%
melts.

00:42:12.240 --> 00:42:17.010 align:middle line:84%
And I know that what
is so now is so forever

00:42:17.010 --> 00:42:22.322 align:middle line:84%
and that I'm just part
of an evolving life.

00:42:22.322 --> 00:42:24.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Before I let you go, I'd
like to talk a little bit about

00:42:24.780 --> 00:42:26.280 align:middle line:90%
the Omega Institute.

00:42:26.280 --> 00:42:28.430 align:middle line:90%
How did that begin?

00:42:28.430 --> 00:42:31.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Omega began an idea in
a few young people's minds.

00:42:31.730 --> 00:42:33.740 align:middle line:84%
We were-- one of
us was a doctor.

00:42:33.740 --> 00:42:34.890 align:middle line:90%
We were in education.

00:42:34.890 --> 00:42:36.590 align:middle line:90%
We were in spirituality.

00:42:36.590 --> 00:42:40.730 align:middle line:84%
And we were a little
ahead of the wave.

00:42:40.730 --> 00:42:42.280 align:middle line:84%
We didn't really
know it at the time.

00:42:42.280 --> 00:42:44.510 align:middle line:84%
We were just interested
in these things, which

00:42:44.510 --> 00:42:48.230 align:middle line:84%
by now are household
words in America-- yoga,

00:42:48.230 --> 00:42:50.660 align:middle line:90%
holistic health, meditation.

00:42:50.660 --> 00:42:54.530 align:middle line:84%
These were very out there
subjects in those days.

00:42:54.530 --> 00:42:57.110 align:middle line:84%
We started very small,
couple of hundred people.

00:42:57.110 --> 00:43:00.530 align:middle line:84%
We rented a prep school
in upstate New York,

00:43:00.530 --> 00:43:02.570 align:middle line:90%
had about four or five teachers.

00:43:02.570 --> 00:43:07.100 align:middle line:84%
But every year, it surprised
us more than anyone what

00:43:07.100 --> 00:43:08.330 align:middle line:90%
the attendance was like.

00:43:08.330 --> 00:43:11.090 align:middle line:84%
There was a tremendous
response and hunger.

00:43:11.090 --> 00:43:14.120 align:middle line:84%
We would bring teachers like
Elisabeth Kubler-Ross, who

00:43:14.120 --> 00:43:15.980 align:middle line:84%
was bringing the
subject of death

00:43:15.980 --> 00:43:17.930 align:middle line:90%
and dying into medical schools.

00:43:17.930 --> 00:43:19.490 align:middle line:90%
No one knew who she was.

00:43:19.490 --> 00:43:20.480 align:middle line:90%
But we'd read a book.

00:43:20.480 --> 00:43:21.860 align:middle line:90%
And we'd bring her.

00:43:21.860 --> 00:43:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And then it began to catch
on more in the culture.

00:43:24.530 --> 00:43:29.570 align:middle line:84%
Last year, 20,000 people came
to Omega in our summer season.

00:43:29.570 --> 00:43:34.700 align:middle line:84%
So we have grown so fast
and learned on our way

00:43:34.700 --> 00:43:38.150 align:middle line:84%
how to run an organization
as large as we are now.

00:43:38.150 --> 00:43:42.860 align:middle line:84%
>> When you began your serious
spiritual journey, it was what,

00:43:42.860 --> 00:43:44.210 align:middle line:90%
25, 30 years ago?

00:43:44.210 --> 00:43:46.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, it actually started
when you were a little girl.

00:43:46.460 --> 00:43:51.950 align:middle line:84%
But as a grown-up, there
must have been so many times

00:43:51.950 --> 00:43:55.220 align:middle line:84%
when you were the only
woman in the room.

00:43:55.220 --> 00:43:59.810 align:middle line:84%
It had to have not been easy
and sometimes infuriating.

00:43:59.810 --> 00:44:02.480 align:middle line:84%
>> It was so
infuriating at times.

00:44:02.480 --> 00:44:05.300 align:middle line:84%
I would want to get
on top of the table

00:44:05.300 --> 00:44:08.240 align:middle line:90%
and just beat my chest and wail.

00:44:08.240 --> 00:44:10.790 align:middle line:84%
And I remember once
seeing a documentary

00:44:10.790 --> 00:44:14.210 align:middle line:90%
about this Brazilian tribe.

00:44:14.210 --> 00:44:16.700 align:middle line:84%
And their habitat
was being encroached

00:44:16.700 --> 00:44:18.020 align:middle line:90%
upon by an oil company.

00:44:18.020 --> 00:44:21.980 align:middle line:84%
And they marched into
the capital city.

00:44:21.980 --> 00:44:25.300 align:middle line:84%
And the men went with
their spears and war paint.

00:44:25.300 --> 00:44:28.530 align:middle line:84%
And they were like fighting
with the officials.

00:44:28.530 --> 00:44:31.010 align:middle line:90%
And the women took their hands.

00:44:31.010 --> 00:44:33.170 align:middle line:90%
And they circled all the men.

00:44:33.170 --> 00:44:35.210 align:middle line:90%
And they started crying.

00:44:35.210 --> 00:44:36.500 align:middle line:90%
And they started wailing.

00:44:36.500 --> 00:44:39.200 align:middle line:84%
And tears were streaming
down their cheeks.

00:44:39.200 --> 00:44:42.230 align:middle line:84%
And everyone stopped
and looked at them.

00:44:42.230 --> 00:44:46.010 align:middle line:84%
And the head of the tribe said,
the women are speaking for us.

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:47.840 align:middle line:90%
You are hurting us.

00:44:47.840 --> 00:44:51.110 align:middle line:84%
And I often at work
would feel the truth.

00:44:51.110 --> 00:44:54.780 align:middle line:84%
And I would want to express
it the way I know how to.

00:44:54.780 --> 00:44:56.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:44:56.270 --> 00:44:58.760 align:middle line:84%
Many years ago when you
began the Omega Institute,

00:44:58.760 --> 00:45:01.970 align:middle line:84%
you had great
insight as to where

00:45:01.970 --> 00:45:06.050 align:middle line:84%
we were going as a nation
on a spiritual path.

00:45:06.050 --> 00:45:11.540 align:middle line:84%
As we sit here now and you look
forward, where are we headed?

00:45:11.540 --> 00:45:17.000 align:middle line:84%
What difference will all
this have made in our future?

00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:22.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, what I hold as so
hopeful about the coming years,

00:45:22.040 --> 00:45:25.490 align:middle line:84%
what I love the most about what
I see happening in America,

00:45:25.490 --> 00:45:28.610 align:middle line:84%
is that we are
becoming one people,

00:45:28.610 --> 00:45:35.980 align:middle line:84%
that we are learning to
truly appreciate each race,

00:45:35.980 --> 00:45:40.990 align:middle line:84%
each religion, each sex, as
part of this necklace that is

00:45:40.990 --> 00:45:44.260 align:middle line:84%
the world, not that we all
are going to become the same--

00:45:44.260 --> 00:45:45.940 align:middle line:90%
God help us.

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:52.660 align:middle line:10%
That's why I pray that the
mauling of America stops

00:45:52.660 --> 00:45:57.290 align:middle line:10%
and that we do maintain some of
the diversity around the world.

00:45:57.290 --> 00:46:03.220 align:middle line:84%
But what brings me hope is
our becoming one people.

00:46:03.220 --> 00:46:06.910 align:middle line:84%
And to me, it's a metaphor
for becoming unified

00:46:06.910 --> 00:46:10.930 align:middle line:84%
within and without
as the many voices

00:46:10.930 --> 00:46:17.260 align:middle line:84%
that occupy our internal selves,
our childhood, our training,

00:46:17.260 --> 00:46:20.140 align:middle line:84%
becomes one, and we become
a whole strong person,

00:46:20.140 --> 00:46:21.130 align:middle line:90%
and we heal.

00:46:21.130 --> 00:46:24.730 align:middle line:84%
I also see it happening outside
where all the different voices

00:46:24.730 --> 00:46:27.460 align:middle line:84%
in America are
becoming one voice,

00:46:27.460 --> 00:46:31.450 align:middle line:84%
maintaining their
beautiful individuality

00:46:31.450 --> 00:46:33.740 align:middle line:90%
and becoming unified.

00:46:33.740 --> 00:46:39.520 align:middle line:84%
And I think spiritually, you can
see that in religions accepting

00:46:39.520 --> 00:46:40.360 align:middle line:90%
each other.

00:46:40.360 --> 00:46:44.140 align:middle line:84%
But beyond religion, I
think the unity of mankind

00:46:44.140 --> 00:46:47.260 align:middle line:90%
is a spiritual endeavor.

00:46:47.260 --> 00:46:50.020 align:middle line:84%
>> It's certainly gratifying to
see that kind of hopefulness,

00:46:50.020 --> 00:46:51.120 align:middle line:90%
isn't it?

00:46:51.120 --> 00:46:52.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:46:52.630 --> 00:46:53.710 align:middle line:90%
We need hope.

00:46:53.710 --> 00:46:58.660 align:middle line:84%
Hope is a good
emotion to cultivate.

00:46:58.660 --> 00:46:59.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:46:59.500 --> 00:47:00.940 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Elizabeth Lesser.

00:47:00.940 --> 00:47:02.390 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:47:02.390 --> 00:47:03.340 align:middle line:90%
>> You're welcome.

00:47:03.340 --> 00:47:06.390 align:middle line:10%
